{"id":"222370147_Alternating_finite_automata_on_o-words","abstract":"Alternating finite automata on ω-words are introduced as an extension of nondeterministic finite automata which process infinite sequences of symbols. The classes of ω-languages defined by alternating finite automata are investigated and characterized under four types of acceptance conditions. It is shown that for one type of acceptance condition alternation increases the power in comparison with nondeterminism and for other three acceptance conditions nondeterministic finite automata on ω-words have the same power as alternating ones.","authors":["Satoru Miyano","Takeshi Hayashi"],"meta":["December 1984Theoretical Computer Science 32(3):321-330","DOI:10.1016/0304-3975(84)90049-5"],"references":["284100771_Symposium_on_Decision_Problems_On_a_Decision_Method_in_Restricted_Second_Order_Arithmetic","268493389_The_Collected_Works_of_J_Richard_Buchi","268245124_Sets_of_Numbers_Defined_by_Finite_Automata","266548107_Behaviors_of_Processes_and_Synchronized_Systems_of_Processes","266443774_Decidability_of_second-order_theories_and_automata_on_infinite_trees","256720395_On_o-regular_sets","248072786_Theory_of_-languages_I_characterizations_of_-context-free_languages","243076575_Decidability_of_Second-Order_Theories_and_Automata_on_Infinite_Trees","242802691_Theories_of_automata_on_o-tapes_A_simplified_approach","238698002_Decision_Problems_for_omega-Automata","232716889_Theories_of_Automata_on_omega_QTRem-Tapes_A_Simplified_Approach","229334041_o-Computations_on_Turing_machines","222973089_Theory_of_o-languagesI_Characterizations_of_o-context-free_languages","220618274_Alternating_Pushdown_and_Stack_Automata","220574319_Omega-Computations_on_Deterministic_Pushdown_Machines","220574272_Theory_of_omega-Languages_II_A_Study_of_Various_Models_of_omega-Type_Generation_and_Recognition","220431245_Alternation","220287283_Automatentheoretische_und_automatenfreie_Charakterisierungen_topologischer_Klassen_regularer_F